[[Image:Harrat Lunayyir.jpg|thumb|right|240px|View of Harrat Lunayyir from the [[Space Shuttle]]]] '''Harrat Lunayyir''' is a [[lava field]] in northwestern [[Saudi Arabia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.volcano.si.edu/world/volcano.cfm?vnum=0301-04- |accessdate=2010-09-27 |title=Global Volcanism Program - Harrat Lunayyir - Summary |quote=Harrat Lunayyir }}</ref> In 2009 there were swarms of small earthquakes in the area;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/39380701/ns/technology_and_science-science/ |accessdate=2010-09-27 |title=Swarm of Saudi earthquakes raises concerns - Technology & science - Science - OurAmazingPlanet - msnbc.com }}</ref> 2289 people were evacuated from the area.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.volcanolive.com/lunayyir.html |accessdate=2010-09-27 |title=Harrat Lunayyir Volcano, Saudi Arabia - John Seach |date=2009-05-21 }}</ref> Fissures opened on the surface, and the area might now be considered [[Volcano#Active|volcanically active]].
